text: Sampson County is a county in the U.S. state of North Carolina. As of the 2020 census, the county had a population of 59,036. The county seat is Clinton. Sampson County is the second-largest county by land area in North Carolina. ==References== Category:18th-century establishments in North Carolina Category:1784 establishments in the United States Category:North Carolina counties
